# Hemoglobin Subunit Beta (HBB)

Hemoglobin subunit beta is an essential component of the hemoglobin protein complex responsible for oxygen transport in red blood cells. Mutations in this protein are associated with diseases such as sickle cell anemia and beta-thalassemia.

This protein sequence is valuable for mutation studies, comparative proteomics, structural analysis, and protein evolution research. It is commonly used in molecular medicine and biomedical bioinformatics projects.
